TraversA student on the Joseph Campbell Forum recently wrote, “Mary Poppins comes out of nowhere to facilitate other folk’s enlightenment.
She lovingly and wholeheartedly practices compassionate non-attachment.”The student likened Mary Poppins to a bodhisattva.
P. L. Travers was not keen on the first Mary Poppins (1964) starring Julie Andrews.
It would take her estate and death to grant rights for Mary Poppins Returns (2018).
In the Return, Mary Poppins, played flawlessly by Emily Blunt, is a key into the ineffable mysteries.